locked":false,"title":"Bundle dynamically selected libstdc++","user":{"login":"sloede","id":3637659,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM2Mzc2NTk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3637659?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/sloede","html_url":"https://github.com/sloede","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sloede/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sloede/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sloede/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sloede/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sloede/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sloede/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sloede/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sloede/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sloede/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"body":"Julia by default uses [`libstdcxxprobe()`](https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/blob/8de80bdf902e0899dd3e39636a95769cf44c823b/cli/loader_lib.c#L254) on Linux systems to figure out whether to load the system `libstdc++` or the one bundled with Julia. Not doing this can cause problems if other libraries used by a Julia process are compiled against a system libstdc++ that is newer than the one provided by Julia

PackageCompiler currently always bundles the library shipped with Julia, not honoring the dynamic selection. This PR aims to remedy this by searching for the `libstdc++` that will be bundled in the directory where the currently loaded `libstdc++` resides.

